    Outcome Codes (Version 23.01.2023)

    OutcomeCodes.Rd
    Code

    unique alpha numeric code

    Pillar

    concepts in the highest level in the outcome hierarchy

    Pillar.Code

    currently a duplicate of Pillar

    Subpillar

    concepts in the intermediate level of the outcome hierarchy. Subpillar is nested under Pillar

    Subpillar.Code

    short code corresponding to the Subpillar name for use in plotting

    Indicator

    concepts in the intermediate level of the outcome hierarchy. Indicator is nested under Subpillar

    Indicator.Code

    short code corresponding to the Indicator name for use in plotting

    Subindicator

    concepts in the lowest and most detailed level of the outcome hierarchy. Subindicator is nested under Indicator

    Subindicator.Short

    shorter name for the Subindicator

    Subindicator.Code

    short code corresponding to the Subindicator name for use in plotting

    Definition

    description of pthe Subindicator

    Notes

    free text used to clarify the defition of the Subindicator

    Example.units

    example of units that are collecting for that Subindicator

    Original.Outcome

    currently NA

    Negative.Values

    indicates whether the outcome can have negative values; N- No and Y-Yes

    Sign

    indicates whether the outcome is positive or negative

    TC.Ratio

    this is the ratio between the outcome for the treatment and control. TC = TreatmeantControl

    ... 
    OutcomeCodes

    Format

    An object of class data.table (inherits from data.frame) with 115 rows and 19 columns.

    ERA Project Team (2021)
